cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.LO, cs.PL

The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to automatically translate English descriptions of puzzles into answer set programming (ASP) and solve them. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also involves ontology and logic programming, which makes cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) possible sub-categories.
